    "body": "Good question @MishkaRogachev thanks for raising. It makes sense to me for the message to appear on both sides, clarifying the users are now mutual contacts again (beyond the change in state of the message input). \r\n\r\nI've added these screens to the flows to clarify. Essentially, the person being added as a contact again will see `[Display name] sent you a Contact Request` with 2 buttons below `Accept Contact Request` and 'Reject Contact request'. Once they have approved, they will see the message '[Display name] added you as a contact'\r\n\r\nDesigns:\r\nhttps://www.figma.com/file/17fc13UBFvInrLgNUKJJg5/Kuba%E2%8E%9CDesktop?type=design&node-id=30308-623451&t=kJ4J9p6CmvTOMCnD-4\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1440\" alt=\"01-AcceptCR\" src=\"https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/assets/110033914/1911fb32-de9a-4ccb-b051-98d93a6ead7c\">\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1440\" alt=\"02-AcceptedCR\" src=\"https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/assets/110033914/4038f54b-7453-4a72-a5f0-50cbb6c1823a\">\r\n\r\ncc @John-44 for confirmation on the above :)\r\n\r\n",
